### **6. Additional Features**

Most of these are integrated into the C++ backend code and configuration provided above.

*   **Authentication/Authorization:** Implemented using JWT in `AuthMiddleware.h` and `JWTUtils.h`, managed by `AuthManager.cpp`.
*   **Logging and Monitoring:** Integrated using `spdlog` in `Logger.h` and used throughout the application. Log files are persistent via Docker volumes.
*   **Error Handling Middleware:** Implemented in `ErrorMiddleware.h` to catch exceptions and return consistent JSON error responses. `DataVizError` provides structured error codes.
*   **Caching Layer:** `LRUCache.h` provides a generic, thread-safe LRU cache. This could be integrated into `DatasetService` or `DashboardHandler` to cache frequently requested dataset metadata or dashboard configurations.
    *   **Example Integration in `DashboardHandler` (Conceptual):**
        ```cpp
        // In DashboardHandler.h
        #include "utils/Cache.h"
        // ...
        class DashboardHandler {
            DataVizPro::LRUCache<std::string, DataVizPro::Dashboard> dashboard_cache;
            // ...
            crow::response handleGetDashboard(const crow::request& req, const std::string& dashboard_id, AuthMiddleware::context& ctx);
        };

        // In DashboardHandler.cpp (handleGetDashboard)
        // ...
        auto cached_dashboard = dashboard_cache.get(dashboard_id + "_" + ctx.user_id);
        if (cached_dashboard.first) {
            res.code = 200;
            res.write(cached_dashboard.second.toJson().dump());
            LOG_DEBUG("Dashboard ID {} served from cache.", dashboard_id);
            return res;
        }

        Dashboard dashboard = getDashboardByIdAndUser(dashboard_id, ctx.user_id);
        dashboard_cache.put(dashboard_id + "_" + ctx.user_id, dashboard); // Cache it
        // ...
        ```
*   **Rate Limiting:** `RateLimiter.h` provides a token bucket (or similar) rate limiter. It can be integrated into `main.cpp` as a global middleware or on specific routes.
    *   **Example Integration in `main.cpp` (Conceptual):**
        ```cpp
        // In main.cpp, after app definition
        RateLimiter global_rate_limiter(100, std::chrono::minutes(1)); // 100 requests per minute

        // Example: Apply to a specific route handler (could be a custom Crow middleware)
        CROW_ROUTE(app, Constants::API_VERSION + "/datasets").methods("POST"_method)(
            [&](const crow::request& req, AuthMiddleware::context& ctx) {
                // Rate limit by user ID or IP
                std::string rate_limit_key = ctx.user_id.empty() ? req.remote_ip_address : ctx.user_id;
                if (!global_rate_limiter.allow(rate_limit_key)) {
                    throw DataVizError(ErrorCode::SERVICE_UNAVAILABLE, "Too many requests", "Rate limit exceeded", 429);
                }
                return dataset_handler.handleUploadDataset(req, ctx);
            }
        );
        ```

